cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the performance of tracking algorithms, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves learning a deformable convolution filter, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision for object detection and recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of sub-filters and their relative locations suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
